WEBVTT

00:38.746 --> 00:41.115
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

00:45.454 --> 00:48.114
(SCREAMING)

00:48.150 --> 00:49.783
(ALL SCREAMING)

00:55.058 --> 00:56.090
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

00:56.126 --> 00:58.330
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:08.203 --> 01:10.342
(ALL CHEERING)

01:13.111 --> 01:14.643
MAN 1: All aboard, girls!

01:15.945 --> 01:17.778
Bye!

01:50.179 --> 01:51.383
(BUS HONKING)

01:54.849 --> 01:57.391
MAN 2: Welcome home, honey!
GIRL 1: Hi, Daddy!

01:57.426 --> 01:58.250
Hi, Mom!

01:58.286 --> 02:00.054
-Mom!
-Hi!

02:00.089 --> 02:02.526
Hi! (LAUGHS)

02:03.898 --> 02:05.765
Wait. Did you get taller?

02:05.800 --> 02:07.361
-Yes, I did.
-Wow.

02:07.396 --> 02:09.002
So good. Okay. Oh, here it is.

02:09.037 --> 02:10.402
-Let's get your trunk.
-MARGARET: Yes.

02:10.437 --> 02:13.203
I double-parked the car
and they're already mad at me.

02:13.239 --> 02:15.138
-What car?
-Oh, we bought a car.

02:15.174 --> 02:16.569
-We bought got a car?
-Yeah!

02:16.604 --> 02:18.342
-What for?
-I'll explain later.

02:18.377 --> 02:19.573
It's that big blue one
right over there.

02:19.609 --> 02:20.940
-(HONKING)
-In the middle of the road.

02:20.975 --> 02:22.579
-MAN 3: Hey, lady,
you kidding me?
-BARBARA: Sorry!

02:22.615 --> 02:23.945
-Sorry, we're going.
One second.
-There's my girl!

02:23.980 --> 02:25.478
Grandma!

02:25.513 --> 02:27.417
-Ah!
-(HONKING CONTINUES)

02:27.452 --> 02:29.885
-Oh, God, I missed you!
-MARGARET: Me, too!

02:29.920 --> 02:31.556
Lady, you can't stop
in the middle of the street.
Let's go!

02:31.591 --> 02:33.055
-I'm sorry. Promise,
two more seconds.
-Come on, lady.

02:33.090 --> 02:34.159
Welcome home gift.

02:34.194 --> 02:35.861
-Oh, you made this?
-From scratch.

02:35.896 --> 02:37.058
-Aw!
-It's cashmere.

02:37.094 --> 02:38.129
I did everything

02:38.164 --> 02:39.530
-but shave the goat.
-(GIGGLES)

02:39.565 --> 02:41.101
-Margaret! Can you just...
-MAN 3: Let's go, ladies.

02:41.136 --> 02:43.399
I'm so sorry. Yeah,
get the bottom there.

02:43.434 --> 02:45.600
-Okay. You got it.
-Here we go. Okay.

02:45.635 --> 02:47.366
-Right on, girls.
-All right, here we go.

02:47.402 --> 02:49.236
-Oh, God.
-Heavy.

02:49.272 --> 02:50.504
Watch out for the...

02:50.540 --> 02:53.042
-Watch out for the bike.
-Oh, God.

02:53.078 --> 02:54.609
BARBARA: Here we go.

02:54.644 --> 02:57.012
Whoa, whoa, whoa, hey.
I would've done it.

02:57.048 --> 02:58.183
BARBARA: Oh, hi!

02:58.218 --> 03:00.119
I would've done it.
Please, please.

03:00.154 --> 03:02.284
-Oh, my God. Amazing.
-We got it.

03:02.320 --> 03:04.617
-Dad!
-Hello! Oh, my goodness!

03:04.653 --> 03:07.190
-I'm so glad to see you.
-Me, too!

03:07.225 --> 03:08.522
Look at that! What happened?

03:08.558 --> 03:10.325
-So, how was camp?
-It was amazing.

03:10.361 --> 03:11.392
-So, you were in a play?
-Yep!

03:11.427 --> 03:13.398
Oh, my God. That's incredible.

03:13.434 --> 03:14.967
-What are those boxes for?
-Don't worry about that.

03:15.003 --> 03:16.033
I want to hear
more about camp.

03:16.068 --> 03:17.169
What else did you learn?

03:17.204 --> 03:18.470
-What else did you do?
-You're moving.

03:20.369 --> 03:21.568
-What?
-Really, Mom?

03:21.604 --> 03:23.541
-Sylvia. You promised.
-Oh, wow.

03:23.976 --> 03:25.011
We're moving?

03:25.047 --> 03:26.274
Look, it's...
Look, we we're...

03:26.310 --> 03:27.677
SYLVIA: She saw the boxes.

03:27.712 --> 03:29.211
-She was putting it together.
-I don't think she was.

03:29.246 --> 03:30.749
-We're moving?
-Okay.

03:30.785 --> 03:32.150
HERB: Just...

03:32.186 --> 03:34.183
Look, we wanted you
to settle in

03:34.219 --> 03:35.682
before we sprung the news.

03:35.717 --> 03:37.819
But, um, your dad
got his promotion.

03:37.854 --> 03:40.292
HERB: Yeah. Isn't that great?
BARBARA: And we found

03:40.328 --> 03:41.355
-this great house.
-HERB: Oh, the best house.

03:41.390 --> 03:42.725
-The best house.
-Where?

03:42.760 --> 03:45.426
Well, that's the thing.
We got really lucky. And...

03:45.461 --> 03:47.697
-New Jersey.
-HERB: Ah...

03:49.038 --> 03:51.303
-New Jersey?
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

03:51.338 --> 03:53.268
-(HERB GROANS)
-I said I'd stay out of it.

03:53.303 --> 03:55.006
We're leaving New York?

03:55.041 --> 03:56.803
Barely leaving New York.

03:56.838 --> 03:58.908
It's just on the other side
of the river.

03:58.943 --> 04:00.314
But...

04:01.316 --> 04:03.042
But we're happy here.
We don't need to move.

04:03.078 --> 04:05.750
No, we don't need to move
but we want to move. Right?

04:05.785 --> 04:06.812
I don't.

04:06.847 --> 04:10.053
I'll have to leave
all of my friends

04:10.088 --> 04:11.685
and change schools

04:11.720 --> 04:14.058
and I'll never
see Grandma anymore.

04:14.094 --> 04:15.559
BARBARA: That is not true.

04:15.595 --> 04:17.090
Look, you're going to keep
all your friends here

04:17.125 --> 04:20.659
and you're going to make more
friends. And listen to this.

04:20.694 --> 04:22.435
I'm not going to work anymore.

04:23.268 --> 04:25.405
Do you know what that means?

04:25.440 --> 04:28.073
That means that I'm not going
to be gone all the time.

04:28.108 --> 04:30.540
Running from class to class.

04:30.575 --> 04:33.809
God. Do you know how
bad I felt about that?

04:35.082 --> 04:37.318
But you love teaching art.

04:38.252 --> 04:42.518
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, I do, I do, but...

04:42.553 --> 04:45.557
But this is,
this is our opportunity.

04:46.388 --> 04:47.821
I'll be home now.

04:47.856 --> 04:51.625
I can be home with you
every single day.

04:51.661 --> 04:53.330
I'll get involved
at your school,

04:53.366 --> 04:55.127
just like
all your friends' moms.

04:55.162 --> 04:58.803
And we'll have family dinners
and I'll learn to cook.

04:58.839 --> 04:59.868
(CHUCKLES)

05:00.602 --> 05:02.002
BARBARA: I know it's a lot.

05:03.210 --> 05:04.972
Can you just
try to believe us?

05:08.012 --> 05:09.075
Yeah.

05:11.048 --> 05:12.045
Mmm.

05:13.582 --> 05:15.683
I love you so much. Come here.

05:15.718 --> 05:19.854
Come here. You, too.
And you, Sylvia.

05:19.890 --> 05:22.394
-Sylvia. Come on.
-HERB: Come on, Mom. Come on.

05:22.429 --> 05:25.060
BARBARA: Come on.
You know you want to.

05:25.095 --> 05:26.232
Faster.

05:26.267 --> 05:28.598
Okay, okay,
I'm coming, I'm coming.

05:28.634 --> 05:30.932
BARBARA: There we go.
SYLVIA: Oh, my darling.

05:32.108 --> 05:34.037
I'm never
going to see you again.

05:34.073 --> 05:35.471
HERB: Oh, Jesus.

05:35.507 --> 05:38.574
-Wow.
-So dramatic all the time.

05:38.609 --> 05:39.838
What are you
taking her over there

05:39.874 --> 05:41.378
with the schmucks
and the condos

05:41.414 --> 05:42.644
on the other side
of the Hudson?

05:42.680 --> 05:43.710
But we're not going to be
in a condo.

05:43.746 --> 05:45.249
SYLVIA: And those
mafia diners,

05:45.284 --> 05:46.414
where they shoot each other...

05:46.449 --> 05:47.481
(ARGUING INDISTINCTLY)

05:47.516 --> 05:48.785
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

05:49.419 --> 05:50.886
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

06:07.975 --> 06:09.872
(SIGHS) God...

06:13.242 --> 06:15.009
(SIGHS)

06:22.317 --> 06:23.688
God?

06:28.458 --> 06:30.024
Are you there, God?

06:31.231 --> 06:35.733
It's me... Margaret Simon.

06:38.707 --> 06:39.836
Um...

06:42.307 --> 06:44.203
I just wanted... Well...

06:45.878 --> 06:48.680
First, I've, I've heard a lot
of great things about you.

06:52.614 --> 06:54.916
I don't want to move.

06:54.951 --> 06:57.920
I've never lived anywhere
but the city, and...

06:58.786 --> 07:01.258
I... I don't want to do this.

07:01.293 --> 07:03.155
Please, I'm begging you.

07:03.191 --> 07:06.093
Just please, just stop
this move from happening.

07:10.635 --> 07:14.233
Um, if...
if you can't do that...

07:16.237 --> 07:20.613
Just please don't let
New Jersey be too horrible.

07:30.420 --> 07:32.526
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

07:33.523 --> 07:35.727
(GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING)

07:52.142 --> 07:55.142
-You're gonna have
to hurry up, all right?
-Okay, Dad!

07:56.018 --> 07:58.013
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

08:05.258 --> 08:06.857
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

08:17.164 --> 08:20.002
BARBARA: Okay, you.
You need some light.

08:22.208 --> 08:24.303
(SNIFFS) Oh, God.

08:25.178 --> 08:26.774
They smell bad?

08:26.810 --> 08:28.475
Oh, they don't
smell good, honey.

08:28.511 --> 08:32.415
-You're going to be there
very soon. Believe me.
-(DOORBELL RINGS)

08:32.450 --> 08:33.785
MARGARET: I'll get it.

08:36.083 --> 08:37.552
I already know
your name's Margaret

08:37.588 --> 08:38.753
and you're in sixth grade.

08:38.789 --> 08:40.187
The real estate agent
sent out,

08:40.223 --> 08:42.055
like, a tiny flyer about you
to the whole neighborhood.

08:42.091 --> 08:44.191
It was, like, this big
and it had your picture.

08:45.032 --> 08:46.497
Oh, okay.

08:46.533 --> 08:48.665
I'm Nancy.
I'm in sixth grade, too.

08:48.700 --> 08:49.798
Do you want to
come over to my house

08:49.833 --> 08:51.499
and run under
the sprinklers with me?

08:51.534 --> 08:54.072
Oh. I don't know.

08:54.108 --> 08:55.607
You don't know?

08:55.643 --> 08:59.474
Oh, no, no, no.
I just mean I'll have to ask.

08:59.509 --> 09:01.307
Um, just a second.

09:02.743 --> 09:03.977
-Mom?
-Yeah?

09:04.012 --> 09:05.377
There's a girl
from the neighborhood

09:05.412 --> 09:07.483
who asked if I could go
under the sprinklers with her.

09:07.518 --> 09:09.782
Oh, that's great. Yeah.

09:09.817 --> 09:11.422
I need my bathing suit.

09:11.457 --> 09:12.724
Good luck finding it in here.

09:12.759 --> 09:15.090
That's all right.
She can borrow one of mine.

09:16.426 --> 09:18.226
Oh, hello.

09:18.261 --> 09:21.232
Nancy Wheeler.
I live in the bigger house
up the street.

09:21.267 --> 09:22.262
Come on, let's go.

09:28.674 --> 09:30.910
Whose class are you in
at Delano?

09:30.945 --> 09:32.107
Um...

09:32.940 --> 09:35.180
The letter said "Room 18."

09:35.216 --> 09:37.384
I'm in room 18, too!

09:37.419 --> 09:38.683
We were supposed to have
Miss Phipps,

09:38.718 --> 09:40.718
but she ran off
with some guy to California,

09:40.753 --> 09:42.221
so we're going to get
a new teacher now.

09:42.257 --> 09:44.383
Come on. Room's upstairs.

09:49.557 --> 09:50.763
Voila.

09:52.234 --> 09:53.392
My bathing suit's over here.

09:55.629 --> 09:57.435
Um...

09:57.470 --> 09:59.836
-Here. It's clean.
-Thanks.

09:59.872 --> 10:02.643
-Where should I change?
-What's wrong with here?

10:04.139 --> 10:07.378
Nothing. I don't mind
if you don't mind.

10:07.414 --> 10:08.979
(SCOFFS) Why would I mind?

10:23.494 --> 10:25.061
You're still flat.

10:25.593 --> 10:26.630
Um...

10:26.665 --> 10:29.197
Well, I'm already growing.
See?

10:30.198 --> 10:32.002
I'm going to have
a pretty big chest.

10:34.905 --> 10:36.201
You know,
coming from New York,

10:36.237 --> 10:38.443
I thought you'd be
a lot more grown up.

10:38.478 --> 10:39.779
Have you ever kissed a boy?

10:40.814 --> 10:43.577
You mean, like, really kiss?
Like, on the lips?

10:43.613 --> 10:45.686
Yeah. Have you?

10:46.285 --> 10:48.048
Not exactly.

10:48.083 --> 10:51.090
Neither have I,
but I practice a lot.

10:51.126 --> 10:52.451
You want to see?

11:01.697 --> 11:03.132
(KISSING LOUDLY)

11:10.540 --> 11:13.947
(LAUGHING)

11:13.982 --> 11:15.007
What?

11:15.043 --> 11:16.142
-Sorry.
-You have to practice

11:16.177 --> 11:18.180
or else you won't
be a good kisser.

11:19.648 --> 11:21.084
Ready to go?

11:22.023 --> 11:22.850
Sure.

11:22.885 --> 11:24.223
(60'S FRENCH MUSIC PLAYING)

11:24.258 --> 11:26.122
Follow the leader.

11:27.657 --> 11:29.026
Yeah, watch me.

11:39.306 --> 11:40.334
(BOTH LAUGHING)

11:42.036 --> 11:44.008
-I'm a supermodel.
-Okay.

11:46.641 --> 11:47.839
(YELPS)

11:47.875 --> 11:48.944
(BOYS LAUGHING)

11:48.979 --> 11:51.650
-Evan, you stupid idiot!
-I'm sorry.

11:51.686 --> 11:53.284
You're such a great model,
by the way.

11:53.320 --> 11:54.352
Who are they?

11:54.388 --> 11:55.487
It's my dumb brother

11:55.523 --> 11:56.521
-and his stupid friend.
-Hey.

11:56.557 --> 11:58.454
-Mom!
-That was uncalled for.

11:58.489 --> 11:59.485
Who are you?

12:00.662 --> 12:02.989
Margaret. Um, we moved in
down the street.

12:03.024 --> 12:04.631
Oh, so you're the new people?

12:04.666 --> 12:06.058
Ask your dad if he wants me
to cut the lawn.

12:06.093 --> 12:07.634
Five bucks, and I trim, too.

12:07.669 --> 12:10.133
MRS. WHEELER: Evan!
Get over here right now!

12:10.868 --> 12:12.333
-(SIGHS) I got to go.
-Dude...

12:14.736 --> 12:15.974
(BOY GRUNTS)

12:21.449 --> 12:23.047
Got to get us more birdseed.

12:23.645 --> 12:25.281
Yeah.

12:25.316 --> 12:28.549
My name's Moose. Moose Freed.
I live down the street, too.

12:28.584 --> 12:29.823
Um...

12:30.856 --> 12:31.984
Yeah, but don't forget
to ask your dad

12:32.019 --> 12:33.860
about the lawn thingy.

12:34.429 --> 12:36.159
Yeah. (CHUCKLES) I won't.

12:37.226 --> 12:38.958
(SIGHS) Oh,
now I got to go see Evan.

12:38.993 --> 12:40.900
(GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING)

12:43.539 --> 12:45.237
Sorry you got stuck
with Moose.

12:45.273 --> 12:47.137
Oh, that's okay.

12:47.805 --> 12:50.204
Anyways, listen, Margaret.

12:50.240 --> 12:52.845
I've decided I want you
to join my secret club.

12:52.881 --> 12:55.447
There's three of us
and I'm letting in one more.

12:55.482 --> 12:56.616
But you can't wear socks

12:56.652 --> 12:58.115
or else the others
might not want you.

12:58.680 --> 12:59.919
Oh.

13:00.684 --> 13:01.781
See you later.

13:01.816 --> 13:03.021
(DOOR OPENS)

13:05.126 --> 13:07.927
MARGARET:<i> Are you there, God?</i>
<i>It's me, Margaret, again.</i>

13:13.295 --> 13:14.994
It's the first day
of school tomorrow.

13:15.029 --> 13:16.669
I met this girl, Nancy.

13:16.704 --> 13:18.972
I don't really know
if she liked me.

13:19.007 --> 13:24.570
I think she just expected me
to be different or something.

13:26.208 --> 13:29.976
Anyway, well,
it did get me thinking.

13:30.011 --> 13:33.312
Maybe it is time for...

13:33.347 --> 13:37.356
things to be happening
around here?

13:37.391 --> 13:38.419
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

13:39.127 --> 13:40.157
Come in.

13:41.294 --> 13:43.358
Look.

13:43.394 --> 13:44.896
MARGARET:<i> Anyway, just think</i>
<i>about what I mentioned.</i>

13:44.931 --> 13:46.027
BARBARA: It was in
with the bathroom stuff.

13:46.063 --> 13:47.631
I found this, too,
if you need it.

13:47.666 --> 13:48.699
MARGARET:<i> Thanks, God.</i>

13:48.734 --> 13:50.535
-Thanks, Mom.
-Mmm-hmm.

13:50.570 --> 13:51.971
(LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING)

13:52.770 --> 13:54.568
Oh, wow, look at you.

13:54.604 --> 13:57.543
BARBARA: Are you ready
for your first day?
How you feeling?

13:57.578 --> 13:59.176
It's going to be great, right?

13:59.212 --> 14:02.812
And if it's not great, first
days don't count anyways.

14:02.847 --> 14:04.047
-Right?
-BARBARA: Exactly.

14:04.082 --> 14:05.312
-HERB: All right.
See you later.
-Bye!

14:05.348 --> 14:08.320
-HERB: Bye!
-Did I not
unpack your socks?

14:08.356 --> 14:10.983
Oh, um, uh...

14:11.019 --> 14:12.051
I don't want socks.

14:12.087 --> 14:14.260
Why? You'll get blisters.

14:14.296 --> 14:15.588
I just don't.

14:16.497 --> 14:18.465
(SUCKS TEETH) Okay.

14:18.500 --> 14:19.761
(LAWN MOWER STARTS OUTSIDE)

14:19.796 --> 14:21.297
Oh. Oh, wait. Dad!

14:22.899 --> 14:25.064
-Hey, hey, Dad!
-Yeah!

14:25.099 --> 14:26.599
-Hey. Um...
-Hey.

14:28.003 --> 14:29.135
I forgot to ask you.

14:29.170 --> 14:30.809
Um, a boy named Moose asked

14:30.844 --> 14:32.977
if he can cut our lawn
for five bucks.

14:33.013 --> 14:35.713
Moose? Well, tell him thanks,
but no, thanks.

14:35.748 --> 14:37.014
I just got a new power mower

14:37.050 --> 14:39.252
and I'm really excited
for the grass to grow.

14:39.288 --> 14:40.615
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

14:40.650 --> 14:42.784
-All right. Knock 'em dead
today, all right, sweetie?
-Okay.

14:42.819 --> 14:44.518
-Okay.
-Bye.

14:46.258 --> 14:48.489
I just need to warn you
one more time about the socks.

14:51.197 --> 14:54.000
-(LIVELY MUSIC CONTINUES)
-(STUDENTS CHATTERING)

15:13.554 --> 15:14.680
Oh, Margaret's here.

15:20.091 --> 15:23.661
Hello. Good,
I thought you'd forget.

15:23.696 --> 15:24.762
Guys, this is Margaret,

15:24.798 --> 15:26.097
the one
I was telling you about.

15:26.133 --> 15:28.262
-Margaret, this is Janie.
-Hi, nice to meet you.

15:28.297 --> 15:30.295
-Yeah, you, too.
-And this is Gretchen.

15:30.331 --> 15:33.168
-So, you're the fourth.
-Yeah.

15:33.204 --> 15:35.237
Well, you're lucky
we saved you a seat.

15:35.273 --> 15:38.110
Or else you'd be sitting
next to Norman Fisher.

15:40.677 --> 15:42.177
Ugh.

15:42.212 --> 15:44.985
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God, don't look.

15:45.818 --> 15:48.316
Philip Leroy just walked in.

15:48.352 --> 15:51.149
I was praying so hard
he'd be in our class.

15:51.185 --> 15:52.586
Who's Philip Leroy?

15:53.461 --> 15:54.654
Take a guess.

16:03.065 --> 16:04.367
Is that our teacher?

16:05.440 --> 16:08.073
Her? (GIGGLES) No.

16:08.108 --> 16:11.044
That's Laura Danker.
Stay away from her, okay?

16:11.711 --> 16:12.945
My brother says that

16:12.980 --> 16:15.113
she goes behind the A&P
with him and Moose

16:15.149 --> 16:17.578
-and lets them feel her up.
-(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

16:20.118 --> 16:22.418
-(DOOR CLOSES)
-(MAN CLEARS THROAT)

16:24.352 --> 16:26.286
Good morning, class.
(CHUCKLES)

16:26.322 --> 16:27.889
First, let me
introduce myself.

16:27.924 --> 16:30.291
I am Mr. Benedict.

16:30.326 --> 16:33.033
And I'm your new
sixth grade teacher.

16:34.231 --> 16:35.629
Please complete
the following sentences

16:35.665 --> 16:39.105
so we can get to know each
other a little better, yeah?

16:39.140 --> 16:42.768
Now, I'll begin, just to
start things off for you guys.

16:43.842 --> 16:45.142
I love that I'm finally

16:45.177 --> 16:47.509
getting to be a teacher
for the first time.

16:49.384 --> 16:50.380
I hate...

16:51.014 --> 16:52.281
feeling self-conscious

16:52.316 --> 16:53.578
trying not to feel
self-conscious because

16:53.614 --> 16:56.251
then you only feel
more self-conscious

16:56.286 --> 16:57.382
and then you're blabbing
in front of

16:57.417 --> 16:58.650
a whole bunch of kids. Um...

16:58.686 --> 17:01.721
I'm looking forward to
the year with you all.

17:02.289 --> 17:04.328
Okay, uh, your turn.

17:14.301 --> 17:15.636
(WHISPERING) Pass it on.

17:22.617 --> 17:24.678
(GROOVY MUSIC PLAYING)

17:28.489 --> 17:30.519
Yes. Okay.

17:37.391 --> 17:39.693
Can any of you go in here?

17:42.766 --> 17:44.203
Ugh, no.

17:45.133 --> 17:46.832
Back in the box.

18:00.952 --> 18:04.657
Okay. All right. Enough.

18:04.692 --> 18:06.489
Enough, enough, enough.

18:17.166 --> 18:18.831
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

18:19.839 --> 18:21.608
-Hello?
-Guess who?

18:21.643 --> 18:23.803
Oh. Sylvia, hi. Um...

18:24.738 --> 18:27.609
-Margaret's not home yet.
<i>-It's 3:32.</i>

18:27.976 --> 18:29.380
<i>Yeah?</i>

18:29.416 --> 18:32.478
You said she's out at 3:15
and the walk is ten minutes.

18:32.514 --> 18:34.554
Yes, I did say that.
But, well...

18:34.589 --> 18:35.549
I'm sure she'll be

18:35.584 --> 18:37.256
walking through that door
any minute now.

18:37.821 --> 18:39.055
Well...

18:39.090 --> 18:41.854
Okay. I guess I'll just wait.

18:42.826 --> 18:43.856
Okay.

18:46.964 --> 18:48.767
So, how are you?

18:48.803 --> 18:52.135
I am fine. I'm good. Yes.

18:52.170 --> 18:54.306
-And how are you?
<i>-Oh, fine.</i>

18:54.341 --> 18:56.635
I read that when you don't
have any loved ones around

18:56.671 --> 18:59.242
your life expectancy
drops drastically,

18:59.277 --> 19:00.908
but, you know,
I've had a good run.

19:00.943 --> 19:02.442
(LAUGHS)

19:02.478 --> 19:05.885
You have.
You really have. Um...

19:05.921 --> 19:08.221
Margaret is here.
Just a second.

19:09.189 --> 19:11.389
-It's Grandma.
-Oh. Where's the Band-Aids?

19:11.987 --> 19:13.418
Mmm.

19:13.453 --> 19:15.224
-Grandma!
<i>-Honey!</i>

19:15.260 --> 19:17.730
How's New Jersey?
Are you okay?

19:17.766 --> 19:19.427
You can tell me the truth.

19:19.463 --> 19:20.959
You know,
it's actually not that bad.

19:22.531 --> 19:26.002
Well, that's great news!
Wonderful news.

19:26.037 --> 19:27.470
Anyway, I was thinking

19:27.506 --> 19:30.436
that you could come visit
the weekend after next.

19:30.471 --> 19:32.074
<i>I'll get tickets to a show.</i>

19:32.109 --> 19:33.440
You can stay overnight,

19:33.476 --> 19:35.275
we'll have
a little slumber party.

19:35.311 --> 19:36.715
That could be fun, right?

19:36.750 --> 19:38.114
Oh, I'd love that.

19:38.149 --> 19:40.449
Oh, I knew you would. Great.

19:40.485 --> 19:42.347
And I'll tell your mother
it was your idea.

19:42.382 --> 19:44.154
-Okay?
<i>-Okay.</i>

19:44.189 --> 19:47.123
-Bye. Bye.
<i>-Bye, sweetheart.</i>

19:47.158 --> 19:48.657
-Bye. (LAUGHS)
<i>-Love you.</i>

19:52.592 --> 19:54.934
Hey, Mom, can I go Nancy's?

19:54.970 --> 19:56.696
Right now?
But you just got home.

19:56.731 --> 19:58.236
I haven't even heard
about your day yet.

19:58.272 --> 20:01.133
-I know, but can I go?
-Can I have one word?

20:01.169 --> 20:03.136
Ugh... Uh?

20:03.172 --> 20:04.241
Is that a word?

20:04.276 --> 20:07.110
-Can I go? Bye.
-Yes, yes, okay, go.

20:07.145 --> 20:09.248
-I love you. Bye!
-Bye!

20:09.284 --> 20:12.215
NANCY: Freddy was like,
"Boom, boom, look at me!"

20:12.250 --> 20:13.679
He's like,
"Make up your mind!"

20:13.714 --> 20:15.384
-She wants attention.
-Obviously.

20:15.419 --> 20:17.349
I know.
With her "boobala joobeelee."

20:17.384 --> 20:19.356
-(LAUGHS)
-Hi!

20:19.391 --> 20:21.327
We were talking about
Laura Danker again.

20:21.362 --> 20:24.457
Yeah. And how she got
even bigger over the summer.

20:24.492 --> 20:26.827
Yeah, she looked so grown up.

20:26.862 --> 20:28.762
NANCY: You know she's worn
a bra since fourth grade?

20:28.798 --> 20:30.667
And I bet you a dollar
she gets her period, too.

20:30.703 --> 20:32.565
GRETCHEN: Well,
I know for sure
someone in the school does.

20:32.601 --> 20:34.835
-How?
-I always check the bins.

20:34.870 --> 20:36.736
-You know those little bins
in the stall?
-Mmm.

20:36.772 --> 20:39.510
All right. Let's get down
to business, huh?

20:40.342 --> 20:41.508
-First of all...
-Thanks.

20:41.544 --> 20:43.610
...this secret club
is a secret.

20:43.646 --> 20:46.478
Nobody tells anybody
what happens here,

20:46.513 --> 20:47.780
-all right?
-Duh.

20:47.816 --> 20:50.022
NANCY: Second, if you want
to be in the club,

20:50.058 --> 20:51.922
then you have to
follow the rules.

20:51.958 --> 20:53.293
What kind of rules?

20:53.328 --> 20:56.054
(SIGHS) Well, I don't know.
I'm thinking of them.

20:57.227 --> 20:59.596
Don't rush me. Hmm.

21:00.669 --> 21:01.929
Oh, I have one.

21:01.964 --> 21:06.405
If you want to be in the club,
then you have to wear a bra.

21:07.941 --> 21:09.200
GRETCHEN: I have one.

21:09.235 --> 21:12.670
If you guys get your period,
you have to tell us about it.

21:12.706 --> 21:14.212
-Yes.
-GRETCHEN: Immediately.

21:14.247 --> 21:15.708
Every detail.
Especially how it feels.

21:15.744 --> 21:18.015
GRETCHEN: Mmm-hmm.
JANIE: Ooh, mine is,

21:18.050 --> 21:19.351
we can make a Boy Book

21:19.387 --> 21:21.053
and write down the names
of the boys that we like.

21:21.089 --> 21:23.448
Mmm-hmm!
What about you, Margaret?

21:23.483 --> 21:24.951
What's your rule?

21:30.059 --> 21:31.330
Um...

21:31.365 --> 21:35.698
Yeah, with the Boy Books,
we have to show them

21:35.733 --> 21:39.966
to each other at every meeting
and we can't ever lie.

21:41.569 --> 21:43.505
-All right.
-(GIGGLES)

21:43.540 --> 21:46.009
NANCY: Let's get
this party rolling.

21:46.045 --> 21:47.075
(SOUL MUSIC PLAYING)

21:47.111 --> 21:48.480
GRETCHEN: Whoo!

22:22.850 --> 22:24.912
(BARBARA EXHALES)

22:25.885 --> 22:27.420
Okay, honey.

22:28.689 --> 22:29.686
(SIGHS)

22:30.925 --> 22:32.792
All right. Mmm. (KISSES)

22:32.827 --> 22:33.855
See you tomorrow.

22:35.963 --> 22:37.155
I want to get a bra.

22:40.602 --> 22:41.698
Oh.

22:43.301 --> 22:44.998
You... You think you need one?

22:46.038 --> 22:47.537
Oh, no. Oh, honey.

22:47.572 --> 22:51.438
I'm so sorry.
No, I just mean that, uh...

22:51.473 --> 22:52.770
Bras are kind of a pain,

22:52.805 --> 22:55.309
so you know, why start sooner

22:55.344 --> 22:56.812
than you need to?

22:58.419 --> 23:01.248
But if you want one,
we... we can get you one.

23:01.283 --> 23:02.488
Well, yeah.

23:03.121 --> 23:04.187
So you want one?

23:04.223 --> 23:05.285
Yes. I already said that.

23:05.320 --> 23:07.955
Right. Okay.

23:07.990 --> 23:12.197
Great. Well, all right.
Well, then, we will do that.

23:12.232 --> 23:15.201
-This week?
-Yes. Good night.

23:15.236 --> 23:19.701
Good night. Good night,
my sweet. Okay.

23:19.737 --> 23:21.501
MARGARET:<i> So glad</i>
<i>that's over with, God.</i>

23:21.536 --> 23:23.069
(LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING)

23:27.510 --> 23:29.207
(PARENTS TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

23:30.879 --> 23:32.650
WOMAN: I'm sorry.
Hold on, just a moment.

23:33.881 --> 23:35.517
Are you here
for the PTA meeting?

23:35.553 --> 23:38.885
Oh, yes. Hi, hi.
I'm Barbara Simon.

23:38.921 --> 23:42.621
Oh, Barbara! I'm Jan Wheeler.
Nancy's mother.

23:42.656 --> 23:44.959
-I met Margaret.
-Oh, oh.

23:44.994 --> 23:46.759
We're just about to get
started, so please come in.

23:46.795 --> 23:48.630
-Have a seat.
-Okay, thank you.

23:48.665 --> 23:49.895
-All right.
-Just anywhere is fine?

23:49.930 --> 23:51.463
-Here. Just right here.
-Okay, okay.

23:51.498 --> 23:53.704
Here we go.

23:55.175 --> 23:57.674
Thank you all for coming.

23:57.710 --> 24:00.411
Delano is nothing without
its dedicated parents.

24:00.446 --> 24:01.772
Let's dive right in
and get started

24:01.808 --> 24:03.477
the way we do every year,

24:03.513 --> 24:05.243
by forming our committees.

24:05.279 --> 24:08.414
First up,
we have the Campus
Improvement Committee.

24:08.450 --> 24:09.480
Any volunteers?

24:09.516 --> 24:11.252
Ooh. Okay.

24:11.288 --> 24:13.488
Oh. Wonderful.

24:13.524 --> 24:16.921
Uh-huh. Barbara,
I got you. Okay.

24:16.957 --> 24:20.533
Next, the Delano
Social Committee.

24:21.034 --> 24:21.859
Sure, yeah. Okay.

24:21.895 --> 24:25.403
-Okay.
-(LAUGHS LIGHTLY) Great.

24:25.438 --> 24:27.738
All right.
The Fundraising Committee.

24:30.209 --> 24:31.340
Good for you, Barbara.

24:31.376 --> 24:32.704
This is going to be great.

24:32.739 --> 24:34.841
All right, pencils down.

24:34.876 --> 24:37.478
Kindly pass
your worksheets forward.

24:37.513 --> 24:39.417
How'd you do, Margaret?

24:39.452 --> 24:40.479
MARGARET: I think
I did pretty good.

24:40.515 --> 24:41.684
All right, uh...

24:41.719 --> 24:44.082
Before the bell,
I want to share some news

24:44.117 --> 24:46.757
that I think will make you all
very happy.

24:46.792 --> 24:49.793
(CHUCKLES) Now that you all
are in the sixth grade,

24:49.828 --> 24:53.891
you'll get to do a full,
year-long research project.

24:53.926 --> 24:55.934
-(STUDENTS GROANING)
-Yes!

24:55.970 --> 24:57.299
BOY: The worst.

24:57.335 --> 24:59.536
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

24:59.571 --> 25:00.666
Margaret, I would like
to talk to you

25:00.702 --> 25:02.669
for a moment after class.

25:02.705 --> 25:05.270
Uh-oh.
What'd you do, Margaret?

25:11.218 --> 25:13.212
-Hi.
-Please have a seat.

25:15.555 --> 25:17.381
So basically,
I'm just having little chats

25:17.417 --> 25:20.059
with each student in advance
of your research projects

25:20.094 --> 25:21.153
to answer any questions

25:21.188 --> 25:23.728
or perhaps guide you
toward a topic of choice.

25:24.392 --> 25:25.563
Oh.

25:25.598 --> 25:27.994
And I read your
getting-to-know-you paper.

25:28.029 --> 25:30.027
And I noticed
under the "I hate" section,

25:30.063 --> 25:32.897
you wrote
"religious holidays."

25:32.932 --> 25:35.971
Which I... I found curious.

25:38.974 --> 25:41.774
If you don't want to share,
you don't...

25:41.809 --> 25:43.148
You don't have to, Margaret.

25:43.183 --> 25:45.176
Oh, no. It's just, um...

25:45.211 --> 25:47.111
I guess I just
don't like those holidays

25:47.146 --> 25:49.355
because I don't
celebrate any of them.

25:49.390 --> 25:51.556
My dad is Jewish
and my mom's Christian,

25:51.592 --> 25:54.493
so instead of picking
which religion I am, uh,

25:54.528 --> 25:56.426
they just decided
that I wouldn't have one

25:56.462 --> 25:58.562
and I can choose
when I grow up.

25:58.597 --> 26:01.731
And have you
given that much thought?

26:01.767 --> 26:03.862
Not really. My grandma
wants me to be Jewish.

26:03.897 --> 26:04.997
And your other grandparents

26:05.032 --> 26:07.198
want you to be Christian,
I imagine.

26:07.233 --> 26:09.140
I don't know.
I've never met them before.

26:09.175 --> 26:10.671
They live in Ohio.

26:10.707 --> 26:12.304
So you've never met them
at all?

26:14.410 --> 26:15.780
-No.
-Oh.

26:16.613 --> 26:20.048
Well, if I may suggest it,

26:20.883 --> 26:22.884
I feel like
"religion" could be

26:22.919 --> 26:25.218
a very compelling
research topic for you.

26:28.826 --> 26:30.262
SYLVIA: (ON PHONE)
<i>Tickets are tenth row,</i>

26:30.297 --> 26:32.728
<i>dead center, very hard to get.</i>

26:32.763 --> 26:34.695
-Tell her that.
-BARBARA:<i> I will.</i>

26:34.731 --> 26:36.867
-Is she excited?
-She's excited.

26:36.902 --> 26:40.101
Well, I mean, is she excited
or is she just excited?

26:40.536 --> 26:42.005
She's excited.

26:42.040 --> 26:44.671
Okay, okay, okay, okay, I'll
let you go. Well, I'm excited!

26:44.706 --> 26:46.745
-Okay, bye.
<i>-Bye.</i>

26:47.774 --> 26:48.843
MARGARET: Hey.

26:48.878 --> 26:50.548
-Hey.
-What happened to the couch?

26:50.584 --> 26:53.584
Uh, it's time to turn over
a new leaf.

26:53.619 --> 26:55.986
I was thinking
maybe something modern?

26:56.021 --> 26:58.557
I don't know. I have to think
about it. How was school?

26:58.592 --> 27:01.091
You're home a little later
than usual, huh?

27:01.126 --> 27:02.759
Yeah.

27:02.794 --> 27:05.995
Hey. How come I've never met
your mom or dad?

27:06.967 --> 27:08.665
Um...

27:08.701 --> 27:10.530
Well, what made you
think about that?

27:10.566 --> 27:12.097
Just wondering.

27:12.132 --> 27:14.801
I mean, I know
that we don't see them

27:14.836 --> 27:16.672
because they're
so far away,

27:16.708 --> 27:18.436
but why don't we
even talk to them?

27:20.775 --> 27:22.907
We just, we just don't.

27:22.942 --> 27:25.212
It's, uh... It's, um...

27:26.319 --> 27:27.779
It's such a long story.

27:27.814 --> 27:29.114
What do you mean?

27:29.149 --> 27:31.852
I mean,
I'll tell you another time.

27:31.887 --> 27:33.825
Why can't you just
tell me now?

27:34.654 --> 27:35.959
(SIGHS)

27:37.228 --> 27:38.225
Um...

27:43.632 --> 27:45.738
(SIGHS) I just...

27:50.474 --> 27:51.909
Look, I just...

27:53.607 --> 27:54.846
Uh...

27:56.116 --> 27:58.176
So, um...

27:58.212 --> 28:01.314
We don't see
my parents because, um...

28:03.422 --> 28:05.153
They don't want to.

28:06.389 --> 28:07.760
What?

28:07.795 --> 28:10.829
My mom and dad are very,
very devout Christians, and...

28:11.529 --> 28:12.961
before you were born,

28:12.996 --> 28:16.527
when your dad
and I first fell in love,

28:16.562 --> 28:21.470
um, they told me that
it would be very hard for them

28:21.505 --> 28:23.171
to, uh, have a...

28:24.209 --> 28:25.206
Sorry.

28:25.839 --> 28:27.844
Jewish son-in-law.

28:27.879 --> 28:29.381
They told me it would be
very hard for them

28:29.416 --> 28:31.945
to have a Jewish son-in-law.

28:31.981 --> 28:34.583
And that
if I wanted to marry him,

28:34.619 --> 28:36.720
that was my business, but

28:36.755 --> 28:39.385
I wouldn't be
their daughter anymore.

28:40.790 --> 28:42.454
But you are their daughter.

28:46.263 --> 28:51.232
Mmm-hmm. (SNIFFLES) I guess,
um, what I mean is that, um...

28:53.708 --> 28:56.204
They just didn't want me
in their life anymore.

28:58.409 --> 28:59.504
So, I'm not.

29:04.279 --> 29:07.919
-(VOICE BREAKING) Mom.
-It's okay. Oh, honey.

29:08.451 --> 29:09.750
(MOANS)

29:09.785 --> 29:11.890
It was a long time ago.

29:13.359 --> 29:14.859
I have you guys.

29:14.894 --> 29:17.560
Okay, you know what?
I took Dad to the station

29:17.595 --> 29:18.896
so we could have the car

29:18.932 --> 29:20.833
because we're supposed to
go shopping, remember?

29:21.631 --> 29:23.299
Remember? Bras?

29:23.335 --> 29:24.562
Whoo-hoo.

29:26.599 --> 29:28.907
MARGARET:<i> Are you there, God?</i>
<i>It's me, Margaret.</i>

29:29.373 --> 29:30.408
(SIGHS)

29:30.443 --> 29:32.105
<i>I can't believe this.</i>

29:32.141 --> 29:34.512
<i>What kind of parents</i>
<i>would do that?</i>

29:34.547 --> 29:36.310
<i>And blame it on religion?</i>

29:37.750 --> 29:40.517
<i>God, please</i>
<i>take care of my mom.</i>

29:40.552 --> 29:41.686
<i>She's a good person.</i>

29:41.722 --> 29:43.921
<i>-She's nice to everyone.</i>
-You're welcome.

29:43.956 --> 29:45.723
MARGARET:<i> Even when</i>
<i>she doesn't need to be.</i>

29:45.758 --> 29:47.057
-Thank you.
-Can't forget about you.

29:48.323 --> 29:50.322
MARGARET:<i> I don't know</i>
<i>why this happened.</i>

29:50.357 --> 29:53.596
<i>But please, somehow,</i>
<i>make it all okay.</i>

29:53.631 --> 29:55.526
And here are the bras.

29:55.561 --> 29:57.835
MARGARET:<i> Oh, also,</i>
<i>I'm getting a bra today.</i>

29:57.871 --> 29:59.839
<i>I'd like something</i>
<i>to put in it, please.</i>

30:00.603 --> 30:01.806
Excuse me.

30:01.841 --> 30:04.808
Uh, we're looking for a bra
for my daughter.

30:04.843 --> 30:08.010
Hmm. Well, we don't have
many that small.

30:08.045 --> 30:10.014
But come with me, dear,
I'll measure you.

30:14.387 --> 30:15.481
Arms up, dear.

30:21.194 --> 30:22.220
Hmm.

30:22.256 --> 30:25.863
Barely a 28.
Not even a double-A.

30:25.898 --> 30:27.227
Your best bet
is going to be to go with

30:27.262 --> 30:29.033
-one of these Gro-Bras here.
-It's okay.

30:29.068 --> 30:31.964
So, one day, when you do grow,
it'll grow with you.

30:32.000 --> 30:33.532
Okay. Thank you very much.

30:33.567 --> 30:36.040
-WOMAN: Sure.
-Thanks, we'll just
go try it on.

30:39.875 --> 30:42.307
-Um...
-Hmm? Oh.

30:42.343 --> 30:44.744
Yeah. Can I just...
I'll just... Yep.

30:44.779 --> 30:46.850
Here we go.

30:46.885 --> 30:49.148
(SIGHS) This is
always the tough bit.

30:49.184 --> 30:51.820
I can't even do this
to this day.

30:51.855 --> 30:55.488
Okay. All right. Can I see?

30:58.493 --> 31:01.566
-How's that feel?
-I cannot wait to take it off.

31:01.601 --> 31:04.200
Yeah. Welcome to womanhood.

31:06.638 --> 31:08.303
(CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

31:13.446 --> 31:14.441
(CHILDREN YELLING)

31:34.499 --> 31:35.662
Oh, hello.

31:35.697 --> 31:36.733
Hello.

31:36.768 --> 31:39.972
Look at you. Working the land.

31:40.738 --> 31:42.172
Heavy machinery, ouch.

31:42.207 --> 31:44.474
Be better if I take
my shirt off or it's too much?

31:44.509 --> 31:45.670
Not for me.

31:46.238 --> 31:47.544
-(ENGINE STARTS)
-Ooh.

31:47.579 --> 31:49.113
There it is, yeah.

31:51.114 --> 31:53.045
You ever been kissed
in the suburbs?

31:53.081 --> 31:54.283
