01:03:24.738 --> 01:03:26.476
<i>Oh, sweetheart.</i>

01:03:26.512 --> 01:03:29.044
I'd love to, I'd love...
But I...

01:03:29.510 --> 01:03:30.507
<i>Well...</i>

01:03:33.585 --> 01:03:35.652
I'm going to be
in Florida then.

01:03:35.687 --> 01:03:38.284
<i>I, uh, I heard about</i>
<i>this hotel</i>

01:03:38.319 --> 01:03:41.850
and there's a lot of people
my age there and, uh...

01:03:41.886 --> 01:03:44.394
Um, okay.

01:03:44.430 --> 01:03:46.589
Wait a minute. Wait. Um...

01:03:47.732 --> 01:03:49.961
What if you
fly down to Florida

01:03:49.996 --> 01:03:51.561
and spend a few days with me?

01:03:51.597 --> 01:03:54.900
<i>-Isn't your spring break soon?</i>
-Yeah. The end of April.

01:03:54.935 --> 01:03:56.967
Perfect! I'll still be there.

01:03:57.002 --> 01:03:58.471
I'll ask Mom and Dad.

01:03:58.507 --> 01:04:00.136
Oh, great!

01:04:00.172 --> 01:04:02.946
<i>That's my girl. Bye, darling.</i>

01:04:05.678 --> 01:04:08.312
(SIGHS)

01:04:08.347 --> 01:04:10.086
NANCY: Come on, come on!
Front row tickets!

01:04:10.121 --> 01:04:13.620
-Front row tickets, remember?
-I'm coming! Yes, coming!

01:04:13.656 --> 01:04:14.719
(SHOW MUSIC PLAYING)

01:04:14.755 --> 01:04:16.058
I'm so excited.

01:04:18.790 --> 01:04:19.996
Hi.

01:04:20.563 --> 01:04:21.899
-Hi.
-Hey.

01:04:30.442 --> 01:04:32.437
(SHOW MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:04:46.051 --> 01:04:48.453
-Excuse me.
-Okay.

01:04:48.788 --> 01:04:49.993
Thank you.

01:04:56.830 --> 01:04:57.932
(MOOSE MUTTERING)

01:04:57.967 --> 01:04:59.937
(SOFT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS)

01:05:03.936 --> 01:05:05.034
Sorry. Lefty.

01:05:05.069 --> 01:05:06.570
Oh, no, it's okay.

01:05:09.814 --> 01:05:11.212
Do you know if
the waiter's anywhere?

01:05:11.247 --> 01:05:14.380
Oh. You can have mine.
I didn't drink any out of it.

01:05:14.813 --> 01:05:16.019
Thanks.

01:05:17.453 --> 01:05:18.450
Hey.

01:05:20.822 --> 01:05:21.956
Do you know something

01:05:21.992 --> 01:05:23.691
I've always liked
about you, Margaret?

01:05:23.726 --> 01:05:25.023
-No?
-Come with me.

01:05:25.058 --> 01:05:26.390
I got to go to the bathroom.

01:05:26.425 --> 01:05:28.493
We'll be right back.
Don't touch my food.

01:05:31.265 --> 01:05:33.270
You know, I've had to go
since we got here...

01:05:33.305 --> 01:05:34.399
(URINATING)

01:05:34.435 --> 01:05:36.437
...and then I drank, like,
three 7Ups or something.

01:05:36.472 --> 01:05:37.902
Uh-huh.

01:05:37.938 --> 01:05:39.636
(FINISHES URINATING)

01:05:41.708 --> 01:05:42.738
Oh, no.

01:05:43.778 --> 01:05:45.114
-Oh, no.
-What?

01:05:45.649 --> 01:05:47.314
Oh, please. Oh, no.

01:05:48.682 --> 01:05:49.712
Nancy?

01:05:51.421 --> 01:05:52.785
Oh, no.

01:05:52.821 --> 01:05:53.985
Nancy, what's wrong?

01:05:54.020 --> 01:05:55.153
Go get my mom, Margaret.

01:05:55.189 --> 01:05:56.890
-What's going on?
-Go get my mom.

01:05:56.925 --> 01:05:58.795
-Please, quick.
-Let me in.

01:05:58.830 --> 01:06:02.028
Please, please just
go get my mom!

01:06:02.064 --> 01:06:04.001
Okay, okay,
I'll be right back.

01:06:06.697 --> 01:06:10.132
Mrs. Wheeler, Nancy's crying.
She needs you.

01:06:10.167 --> 01:06:12.405
Oh, oh. All right.

01:06:18.283 --> 01:06:19.111
Nancy?

01:06:19.147 --> 01:06:21.677
-Nancy?
-Oh, Mom, please help me.

01:06:21.713 --> 01:06:23.985
-Please help me. Please.
-The door's locked, Nancy.

01:06:24.020 --> 01:06:25.384
I can't get in.
You have to unlock it.

01:06:25.420 --> 01:06:28.122
-I can't open it, I can't.
-Yes, you can, Nancy.

01:06:28.157 --> 01:06:30.357
Unlock this door. Come on.
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

01:06:31.858 --> 01:06:33.096
Let me in.

01:06:34.597 --> 01:06:35.626
(SNIFFLES)

01:06:39.900 --> 01:06:40.930
What's going on?

01:06:40.965 --> 01:06:42.464
(SOBS)

01:06:42.500 --> 01:06:44.740
All right, all right,
calm down.

01:06:44.775 --> 01:06:46.237
Calm down, I can't help you.

01:06:46.273 --> 01:06:48.673
Hmm? Hey, look at me.
Calm down.

01:06:48.708 --> 01:06:51.708
I can't help you if you don't
stop crying and talk to me.

01:06:55.454 --> 01:06:57.582
Hey. What is it?

01:06:59.690 --> 01:07:01.256
(WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY)

01:07:05.763 --> 01:07:09.462
Oh. Well, all right. Um...

01:07:11.097 --> 01:07:12.597
Here. We'll just, uh...

01:07:14.505 --> 01:07:15.800
Margaret?

01:07:15.836 --> 01:07:17.170
Margaret.

01:07:17.205 --> 01:07:21.041
Would you get Nancy
a pad, please

01:07:21.076 --> 01:07:23.509
from the dispenser
on the wall?

01:07:25.145 --> 01:07:27.376
She got her period, sweetie.

01:07:27.411 --> 01:07:29.647
Does she always act like that?

01:07:29.683 --> 01:07:33.189
Well, it's her first time.
She's just a little scared.

01:07:46.836 --> 01:07:47.863
Thank you, sweetie.

01:07:49.233 --> 01:07:50.668
All right. Yeah?

01:07:52.774 --> 01:07:53.836
All right.

01:07:55.680 --> 01:07:57.409
Well, you girls wash up.

01:07:57.444 --> 01:08:00.117
I'm going to go tell
the others not to worry.

01:08:03.281 --> 01:08:06.255
Not too long now. Okay?

01:08:37.222 --> 01:08:40.520
MARGARET:<i> Are you there, God?</i>
<i>It's me, Margaret.</i>

01:08:42.123 --> 01:08:44.161
<i>I don't even know what to say.</i>

01:08:45.796 --> 01:08:46.922
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

01:09:05.013 --> 01:09:06.678
I'm going to Florida?

01:09:07.546 --> 01:09:09.912
-Happy birthday.
-Mom. Thank you so much.

01:09:15.460 --> 01:09:16.457
Hey!

01:09:17.554 --> 01:09:19.862
-Happy birthday.
-Thank you.

01:09:19.898 --> 01:09:21.363
Why do we have
different seats?

01:09:21.398 --> 01:09:23.695
He said we're in groups
to study different countries.

01:09:49.659 --> 01:09:51.320
Oh. Hey.

01:09:51.356 --> 01:09:53.928
Hey. Happy birthday.

01:09:53.963 --> 01:09:54.996
-Thanks.
-Oh, and, uh,

01:09:55.031 --> 01:09:58.197
-I got you something.
-Ow!

01:09:58.232 --> 01:10:00.070
It's a pinch to grow an inch.

01:10:00.105 --> 01:10:03.471
And you know where
you need that inch. Hey.

01:10:06.410 --> 01:10:08.770
MARGARET:<i> Are you there, God?</i>
<i>It's me, Margaret.</i>

01:10:08.805 --> 01:10:11.974
<i>I hate Philip Leroy.</i>
<i>I hate him.</i>

01:10:12.009 --> 01:10:15.318
<i>I hate Laura Danker, too!</i>
<i>With her big boobs.</i>

01:10:15.354 --> 01:10:18.255
<i>"Ooh, look at me, everybody,</i>
<i>I'm wearing a sweater."</i>

01:10:19.054 --> 01:10:21.586
<i>I hate Nancy. That liar!</i>

01:10:21.622 --> 01:10:23.324
<i>And Norman Fisher,</i>
<i>the way that he reads</i>

01:10:23.360 --> 01:10:25.956
<i>with his stupid lips</i>
<i>flapping everywhere!</i>

01:10:25.991 --> 01:10:30.095
<i>Please. Please, just hurry up</i>
<i>and get me to Florida!</i>

01:10:30.130 --> 01:10:32.335
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

01:10:36.002 --> 01:10:36.999
(SIGHS)

01:10:38.703 --> 01:10:40.206
Philip and Norman
should be here.

01:10:40.241 --> 01:10:42.573
They make us do all the work.

01:10:42.608 --> 01:10:44.710
What time is your mom
picking you up?

01:10:45.651 --> 01:10:46.744
Not till later.

01:10:46.780 --> 01:10:48.882
I have to go to St. Thomas
for Confession first.

01:10:48.917 --> 01:10:51.553
Confession?

01:10:51.588 --> 01:10:53.554
It's just something you have
to do when you're Catholic.

01:10:54.386 --> 01:10:55.886
What do you confess?

01:10:57.694 --> 01:10:58.691
Things.

01:11:00.128 --> 01:11:02.431
What kinds of things?

01:11:06.671 --> 01:11:07.667
Never mind.

01:11:15.908 --> 01:11:18.007
You're just copying straight
out of the<i> World Book.</i>

01:11:18.750 --> 01:11:20.378
It's four words.

01:11:20.414 --> 01:11:22.918
"Germany invaded
Belgium when..."

01:11:22.954 --> 01:11:24.319
So, you're still cheating.

01:11:24.354 --> 01:11:26.218
Mr. Benedict will know
if you're cheating.

01:11:26.253 --> 01:11:28.856
I'm not cheating! Jeez!

01:11:28.892 --> 01:11:29.887
(WOMAN SHUSHES)

01:11:32.493 --> 01:11:33.961
Quit acting like
you know everything

01:11:33.997 --> 01:11:35.165
and you're so great.

01:11:35.200 --> 01:11:36.660
This has nothing to do
with being great.

01:11:36.696 --> 01:11:38.764
I know all about the stuff
that you do.

01:11:40.301 --> 01:11:41.664
What's that supposed to mean?

01:11:41.700 --> 01:11:43.571
I heard about you
and Moose Freed.

01:11:44.371 --> 01:11:46.034
What about me and Moose Freed?

01:11:46.070 --> 01:11:49.043
Oh, how you and Evan and Moose
go behind the A&P.

01:11:49.078 --> 01:11:50.479
And why would I do that?

01:11:50.515 --> 01:11:54.142
I don't know why you do it.
But I know why they do it.

01:11:54.177 --> 01:11:56.381
So they can feel you up
or something and you let them.

01:11:56.416 --> 01:11:57.786
You're a liar. You're lying!

01:11:57.822 --> 01:11:58.855
I'm not lying.

01:11:58.890 --> 01:11:59.982
You're just like Nancy.

01:12:00.018 --> 01:12:02.854
All you do is pick on people
and make up stories.

01:12:02.889 --> 01:12:04.856
You think I don't know
about you and your friends?

01:12:17.367 --> 01:12:18.907
Laura!

01:12:18.943 --> 01:12:21.508
Wait. Please! Laura!

01:12:21.543 --> 01:12:23.909
-Wait up. Please!
-You think I don't know

01:12:23.944 --> 01:12:26.216
that all of you make fun of me
like it's some kind of game?

01:12:26.251 --> 01:12:27.445
-It's not me.
-Do you think I want to be

01:12:27.480 --> 01:12:29.013
the biggest kid in the class?

01:12:29.049 --> 01:12:32.285
How would you feel if you were
to wear a bra in fourth grade

01:12:32.320 --> 01:12:33.352
and everybody called you names

01:12:33.388 --> 01:12:35.051
just because of
how you looked?

01:12:36.124 --> 01:12:37.394
I don't know.

01:12:40.027 --> 01:12:41.657
(SCOFFS)

01:12:41.692 --> 01:12:44.401
Hey, wait. I really am sorry.

01:12:49.599 --> 01:12:51.474
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

01:12:55.243 --> 01:12:56.809
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

01:13:02.885 --> 01:13:04.047
Laura?

01:13:06.020 --> 01:13:07.050
Laura.

01:13:23.872 --> 01:13:26.641
MARGARET:<i> I'm the worst person</i>
<i>who ever lived, God.</i>

01:13:26.676 --> 01:13:29.578
<i>I picked on Laura Danker</i>
<i>just because I felt mean.</i>

01:13:30.741 --> 01:13:33.375
<i>I don't want to be like Nancy.</i>

01:13:33.410 --> 01:13:36.717
<i>I don't even know if I want to</i>
<i>be friends with her anymore.</i>

01:13:39.356 --> 01:13:41.018
<i>I've been</i>
<i>looking for you, God.</i>

01:13:42.786 --> 01:13:45.160
<i>I looked for you in Temple,</i>

01:13:45.196 --> 01:13:46.727
<i>I looked for you in Church...</i>

01:13:48.264 --> 01:13:49.928
<i>I didn't feel you at all.</i>

01:13:52.596 --> 01:13:54.229
<i>Why? Why, God?</i>

01:13:55.868 --> 01:13:58.937
<i>Why do I only feel you</i>
<i>when I'm alone?</i>

01:14:03.244 --> 01:14:05.546
Yes, my child.

01:14:05.582 --> 01:14:08.111
Do you have something
you'd like to confess?

01:14:10.084 --> 01:14:11.213
Um...

01:14:12.482 --> 01:14:13.721
(SIGHS)

01:14:17.388 --> 01:14:18.754
I...

01:14:18.789 --> 01:14:21.025
I did something really awful.

01:14:23.163 --> 01:14:24.501
And...

01:14:26.696 --> 01:14:28.164
I'm really sorry.

01:14:29.074 --> 01:14:31.105
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

01:14:31.141 --> 01:14:33.136
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

01:14:47.957 --> 01:14:49.625
(SIGHS)

01:14:56.463 --> 01:14:57.930
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:15:00.104 --> 01:15:01.701
HERB:<i> "Dear Barbara,</i>

01:15:01.736 --> 01:15:03.936
"your letter felt like
an answer to prayer.

01:15:03.972 --> 01:15:06.202
"Your father and I have been
thinking about you a lot.

01:15:06.237 --> 01:15:08.872
"We're getting older and
suddenly, more than anything,

01:15:08.907 --> 01:15:12.847
"we'd like to see
our only daughter

01:15:12.882 --> 01:15:15.552
"and finally get to know our
granddaughter, Margaret Ann."

01:15:16.318 --> 01:15:17.351
(HERB CLEARS THROAT)

01:15:17.386 --> 01:15:18.652
"We're flying east next week,

01:15:18.687 --> 01:15:20.521
"and we sincerely hope
you'll let us visit.

01:15:20.556 --> 01:15:22.757
"Love, your mother,
Mary Hutchins."

01:15:26.031 --> 01:15:27.091
(HERB CLEARS THROAT)

01:15:29.496 --> 01:15:30.930
So you sent them a card?

01:15:33.367 --> 01:15:34.934
I don't know why.

01:15:36.666 --> 01:15:38.003
(HERB SIGHS)

01:15:44.513 --> 01:15:45.676
Do you remember
what it was like

01:15:45.711 --> 01:15:47.342
when they just cast you out?

01:15:49.117 --> 01:15:50.183
Yes.

01:15:50.219 --> 01:15:51.214
HERB: Do you?

01:15:52.222 --> 01:15:53.648
Because I remember.

01:15:53.684 --> 01:15:55.020
I know. I know.

01:15:55.855 --> 01:15:58.056
How they treated you
was just...

01:15:58.956 --> 01:16:00.696
-I know.
-How they treated me?

01:16:01.563 --> 01:16:03.594
They think
you're going to hell

01:16:03.630 --> 01:16:05.129
because you married a Jew.

01:16:06.202 --> 01:16:07.362
Think about that.

01:16:08.037 --> 01:16:09.034
I...

01:16:10.105 --> 01:16:11.200
I know.

01:16:11.236 --> 01:16:14.710
Do you really, really want to
open up that door?

01:16:15.344 --> 01:16:16.637
We have a good life.

01:16:16.673 --> 01:16:18.076
Yes. Yes.

01:16:19.477 --> 01:16:20.683
I...

01:16:21.783 --> 01:16:26.183
But what if this means...
they've changed?

01:16:29.490 --> 01:16:30.726
And if they haven't?

01:16:34.528 --> 01:16:36.193
They're my parents.

01:16:38.970 --> 01:16:39.997
HERB: Mmm.

01:16:40.033 --> 01:16:42.100
-The only ones I got.
-They are your parents.

01:16:43.204 --> 01:16:45.304
Oh, God.

01:16:45.340 --> 01:16:48.209
Oh, my goodness.

01:16:48.245 --> 01:16:49.239
BARBARA: I'm sorry.

01:16:51.015 --> 01:16:52.740
(HERB SIGHS)

01:16:52.776 --> 01:16:54.016
What's going on?

01:16:54.052 --> 01:16:55.415
BARBARA: Um...

01:16:55.451 --> 01:16:57.984
-Oh.
-Oh, honey, um...

01:16:59.187 --> 01:17:00.316
Uh...

01:17:02.225 --> 01:17:03.351
We got a letter

01:17:03.387 --> 01:17:06.187
from, um, from my parents,
from your grandparents.

01:17:06.223 --> 01:17:08.090
And they're coming
to visit next week.

01:17:08.125 --> 01:17:10.565
-Next... next week?
-HERB: Mmm-hmm.

01:17:10.600 --> 01:17:12.160
They're really
excited to meet you.

01:17:12.195 --> 01:17:14.165
I won't be here.
I'll be in Florida.

01:17:17.069 --> 01:17:19.000
I'm still going to Florida,
aren't I?

01:17:19.036 --> 01:17:21.872
-Margaret, look...
-No. What?

01:17:21.907 --> 01:17:24.008
I can't even
go to Florida now?

01:17:24.043 --> 01:17:26.182
Come on, I don't even
want to see them.

01:17:26.217 --> 01:17:27.617
I want to see Grandma.

01:17:27.652 --> 01:17:29.848
I know. I know and we will
make this up to you.

01:17:29.883 --> 01:17:31.850
I promise, you will go
to Florida,

01:17:31.886 --> 01:17:34.048
-just another time.
-No, I don't want

01:17:34.083 --> 01:17:35.989
to go to Florida another time.

01:17:36.888 --> 01:17:38.559
Does Grandma know about this?

01:17:38.595 --> 01:17:40.090
No, not yet.
We have to call her.

01:17:40.126 --> 01:17:42.226
Well, I'm not doing it.
You can do it yourself.

01:17:42.261 --> 01:17:44.127
-No, of course. Of course.
-HERB: Let me handle that.

01:17:44.162 --> 01:17:46.362
-No, I will...
-Please let me call. Please.

01:17:52.205 --> 01:17:54.736
-(LOUNGE MUSIC PLAYING)
-MAN: To this beautiful day.

01:17:54.772 --> 01:17:57.607
(PHONE RINGING)

01:17:57.643 --> 01:17:59.045
Just one moment.

01:17:59.847 --> 01:18:01.544
Don't eat all the cheese
without me.

01:18:01.580 --> 01:18:02.850
(CHUCKLES)

01:18:02.885 --> 01:18:05.420
I'm just kidding.
You eat as much as you want.

01:18:05.455 --> 01:18:07.085
Depending on your cholesterol.

01:18:07.120 --> 01:18:09.385
-(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)
-I'm sure it's low.

01:18:14.792 --> 01:18:15.961
Simon residence.

01:18:15.996 --> 01:18:17.659
HERB: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Hi, Mom. Yes. Uh...</i>

01:18:17.694 --> 01:18:19.032
Herb?

01:18:19.067 --> 01:18:20.764
Uh, Margaret's, uh, plan
to come to Florida next week

01:18:20.799 --> 01:18:21.830
isn't going to work out.

01:18:21.865 --> 01:18:23.069
I'm really sorry.

01:18:24.069 --> 01:18:25.742
MARGARET:<i> Just</i>
<i>give me the phone.</i>

01:18:26.771 --> 01:18:27.873
<i>Hey, Grandma.</i>

01:18:27.908 --> 01:18:30.144
Margaret, what happened?
What's going on?

01:18:30.179 --> 01:18:32.078
We...

01:18:32.113 --> 01:18:35.048
We got a letter that my
other grandparents are coming.

01:18:35.983 --> 01:18:39.885
<i>And I just</i>
<i>really wanted to see you.</i>

01:18:39.920 --> 01:18:42.055
Put your mother
on the phone right now.

01:18:43.560 --> 01:18:45.322
-Oh, no...
-BARBARA: It's okay.

01:18:47.999 --> 01:18:48.894
Sylvia.

01:18:48.929 --> 01:18:50.632
What the hell
is going on, Barbara?

01:18:50.667 --> 01:18:53.669
Sylvia, I'm so very sorry
about this

01:18:53.705 --> 01:18:56.869
and I will try and explain it
another time.

01:18:56.905 --> 01:18:58.838
No. You're going to
explain right now.

01:18:58.873 --> 01:19:00.469
I'm sorry, I have to...
I have to go.

01:19:05.080 --> 01:19:07.408
MARGARET:<i> Are you there, God?</i>
<i>It's me, Margaret.</i>

01:19:07.443 --> 01:19:10.017
<i>-I'm absolutely miserable.</i>
-I am so sorry.

01:19:10.052 --> 01:19:12.481
MARGARET:<i> Everything</i>
<i>is going wrong. Everything.</i>

01:19:13.257 --> 01:19:14.757
<i>I'm begging you.</i>

01:19:14.793 --> 01:19:17.822
<i>Make something happen</i>
<i>so that they don't come</i>

01:19:17.857 --> 01:19:19.928
<i>and I can still go to Florida.</i>

01:19:24.530 --> 01:19:25.901
(HUFFS)

01:19:28.639 --> 01:19:30.306
Please, Margaret.
Even if it's fake,

01:19:30.341 --> 01:19:32.435
can you just look happy?

01:19:33.873 --> 01:19:35.837
Or at least not so unhappy?

01:19:35.873 --> 01:19:37.139
(BARBARA SIGHS)

01:19:37.175 --> 01:19:39.208
Why do you
even want to see them?

01:19:39.243 --> 01:19:41.279
After everything
that they did to you?

01:19:43.217 --> 01:19:48.283
Because I want them to see
how great we've done.

01:19:48.319 --> 01:19:51.586
I... And how proud
I am of our family.

01:19:56.632 --> 01:19:58.263
-Hey! Hello.
-(BARBARA SIGHS)

01:19:59.302 --> 01:20:00.331
That's them.

01:20:01.105 --> 01:20:02.102
Okay.

01:20:04.603 --> 01:20:05.600
Hi!

01:20:06.974 --> 01:20:09.608
They might hug you,
I don't know.

01:20:09.643 --> 01:20:11.045
Just be prepared.

01:20:13.350 --> 01:20:14.942
(BARBARA CHUCKLES)

01:20:14.978 --> 01:20:16.145
-Hi!
-Hello!

01:20:16.181 --> 01:20:18.453
Hello. It's so nice
to see you.

01:20:18.488 --> 01:20:20.615
Oh, you too, Barbara.

01:20:22.689 --> 01:20:23.992
-Oh.
-(KISSES)

01:20:29.092 --> 01:20:30.999
-Hi, honey.
-Oh.

01:20:34.465 --> 01:20:37.005
-This must be Margaret Ann.
-BARBARA: Mmm-hmm.

01:20:38.802 --> 01:20:40.069
(KISSES)

01:20:40.104 --> 01:20:41.875
We're very glad to meet you.

01:20:41.910 --> 01:20:44.441
-Yes, we are. Yes, we are.
-Me, too.

01:20:45.281 --> 01:20:46.344
Um...

01:20:47.518 --> 01:20:49.477
Bags! We'll get the bags.

01:20:49.512 --> 01:20:53.050
Um, Herb is just out, uh,
with the car.

01:20:53.085 --> 01:20:55.185
-Yeah, so... Okay.
-PAUL: Okay.

01:20:55.220 --> 01:20:57.525
BARBARA:
Just out here to the right.

01:20:57.560 --> 01:20:59.324
The blue car there. Yep.

01:21:01.331 --> 01:21:02.828
HERB: Hey.

01:21:02.863 --> 01:21:04.632
-Youse okay? Yeah?
-Yeah.

01:21:04.667 --> 01:21:06.128
Mom, Dad, you remember Herb?

01:21:06.163 --> 01:21:07.568
-Yeah. Hello, Herb.
-Hi.

01:21:07.603 --> 01:21:08.768
-How are you?
-Okay.

01:21:08.804 --> 01:21:10.500
-Hi. Nice to see you.
-Hello.

01:21:11.434 --> 01:21:13.174
Um, should I...
I'll take this for you.

01:21:13.210 --> 01:21:14.240
Oh.

01:21:17.645 --> 01:21:18.675
HERB: All right.

01:21:18.710 --> 01:21:20.114
Okay.

01:21:20.982 --> 01:21:22.043
All right.
Should I put these up?

01:21:22.079 --> 01:21:23.513
Oh, yes. Thank you.

01:21:24.921 --> 01:21:28.688
Here we are.
Make yourselves comfortable.

01:21:28.723 --> 01:21:30.624
-Lovely home.
-Yeah!

01:21:30.659 --> 01:21:33.193
Thank you. Yes. Uh...

01:21:33.960 --> 01:21:35.730
Okay. So, uh, Margaret, uh,

01:21:35.766 --> 01:21:36.897
can you show them
to their room?

01:21:36.933 --> 01:21:39.666
And, um, I'll just
get dinner started.

01:21:39.701 --> 01:21:42.532
Sure. Um, up this way.

01:21:46.338 --> 01:21:48.840
MARY: Gosh, you look
just like your mom

01:21:48.875 --> 01:21:50.304
when she was your age.

01:21:50.339 --> 01:21:53.015
MARGARET: Um, yeah. This way.

01:21:57.982 --> 01:21:59.450
(BARBARA SIGHS)

01:22:00.249 --> 01:22:02.754
-(EXHALES) Hi.
-Hey.

01:22:02.789 --> 01:22:03.954
How are you doing?

01:22:03.989 --> 01:22:06.156
Uh... How are you doing?

01:22:06.192 --> 01:22:08.189
Um, I used up
all my small talk

01:22:08.225 --> 01:22:09.598
-in the car.
-Oh, God.

01:22:09.633 --> 01:22:11.968
Do they like sports? TV shows?

01:22:13.431 --> 01:22:15.498
Game shows.
They used to watch game shows.

01:22:15.534 --> 01:22:18.801
-Okay. Game shows, game shows.
-(DOORBELL RINGS)

01:22:18.837 --> 01:22:20.034
HERB: Hmm.

01:22:20.069 --> 01:22:21.670
Um, coming!

01:22:24.514 --> 01:22:25.542
SYLVIA: Herb!

01:22:26.415 --> 01:22:27.277
Mom!

01:22:27.312 --> 01:22:29.646
Baby! Come give
your mom a big hug.

01:22:29.682 --> 01:22:30.885
Oh.

01:22:30.920 --> 01:22:32.719
-Oh. Look at your little face.
-Sylvia?

01:22:32.754 --> 01:22:34.052
Yeah. My mom is here.

01:22:34.088 --> 01:22:35.451
Uh, yes, she is.
What's happening?

01:22:35.486 --> 01:22:37.692
Well, Margaret said
she needed to see me,

01:22:37.727 --> 01:22:38.989
so we flew out from Florida.

01:22:39.025 --> 01:22:40.156
Are your parents here yet?

01:22:40.191 --> 01:22:42.996
Oh. This is Morris Binamin.

01:22:43.031 --> 01:22:45.062
-Rhymes with cinnamon.
-(CHUCKLES)

01:22:45.097 --> 01:22:47.264
-Hi.
-MARGARET: Grandma!

01:22:47.299 --> 01:22:50.202
There's my Margaret!
(LAUGHING) Oh!

01:22:50.237 --> 01:22:52.200
-BARBARA: Did you know?
-I had no... I know.

01:22:52.235 --> 01:22:53.436
I missed you so much!

01:22:53.471 --> 01:22:54.942
MARGARET: I thought
you were in Florida.

01:22:54.977 --> 01:22:56.809
I know. Well,
Florida came to you.

01:22:56.844 --> 01:22:58.143
-(CHUCKLES)
-Uh...

01:22:58.179 --> 01:23:01.545
Mom, Dad, this is Sylvia.
Herb's mom.

01:23:01.580 --> 01:23:05.716
Sylvia, this... These are
my parents, Paul and Mary.

01:23:05.751 --> 01:23:07.248
Hello.

01:23:07.283 --> 01:23:09.157
-Hello.
-(PAUL CHUCKLES)

01:23:11.759 --> 01:23:12.823
We have pot roast.

01:23:12.859 --> 01:23:14.463
SYLVIA: Sure.

01:23:14.498 --> 01:23:16.098
(CUTLERY CLINKING)

01:23:17.128 --> 01:23:18.529
PAUL AND HERB: Mmm.

01:23:19.769 --> 01:23:21.069
-SYLVIA: Mmm.
-Oh, yeah.

01:23:21.105 --> 01:23:23.267
-Dinner is delicious, Barbara.
-Oh, my God, yes.

01:23:23.302 --> 01:23:26.105
-Oh.
-You have definitely improved.

01:23:26.141 --> 01:23:28.407
-It is very nice.
-(LAUGHS) Thank you.

01:23:30.312 --> 01:23:35.247
Well, I have to admit
it was a bit of a jolt, um,

01:23:35.283 --> 01:23:39.488
but it's nice to have
everyone here together.

01:23:39.523 --> 01:23:41.123
The whole family.

01:23:43.354 --> 01:23:45.858
-And Mr. Binamin.
-(LAUGHS)

01:23:45.893 --> 01:23:47.495
Nice to have you, too.

01:23:47.531 --> 01:23:49.362
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:23:50.261 --> 01:23:52.167
<i>-L'chaim.</i>
<i>-L'chaim.</i>

01:23:53.835 --> 01:23:57.237
<i>L'chaim. L'chaim.</i>

01:23:57.273 --> 01:24:00.239
<i>L'chaim. L'chaim. L'chaim.</i>
<i>L'chaim. L'chaim.</i>

01:24:00.274 --> 01:24:02.408
-(MORRIS LAUGHING)
-(IN ENGLISH) To life!

01:24:08.080 --> 01:24:09.080
(BARBARA CLEARS THROAT)

01:24:09.116 --> 01:24:10.647
So, um,
do you watch<i> Jeopardy!?</i>

01:24:15.618 --> 01:24:17.990
MARY: I used to braid
your mama's hair

01:24:18.025 --> 01:24:19.125
when she was a little girl.

01:24:19.160 --> 01:24:21.062
Did your mom
ever braid your hair?

01:24:21.097 --> 01:24:23.595
Um, yeah, she used to do it
all the time.

01:24:23.630 --> 01:24:26.665
I can see she taught you how
to braid with your bracelet.

01:24:26.700 --> 01:24:27.768
Yeah.

01:24:27.803 --> 01:24:29.070
Oh, there's just so much

01:24:29.105 --> 01:24:30.532
we want to get to know
about you, Margaret.

01:24:30.567 --> 01:24:32.574
Twelve years is a lot
to catch up on.

01:24:32.609 --> 01:24:33.769
Yeah. A long time.

01:24:34.470 --> 01:24:37.113
So, uh, we were wondering...

01:24:38.474 --> 01:24:40.213
Do you go to Sunday school?

01:24:40.248 --> 01:24:42.646
Or, uh, have you ever
thought about it?

01:24:43.546 --> 01:24:47.022
-Uh...
-Nope. Never. Not once.

01:24:47.057 --> 01:24:49.655
We asked Margaret
the question, Sylvia.

01:24:49.691 --> 01:24:50.726
Margaret?

01:24:50.761 --> 01:24:51.886
Well, you're wasting your time

01:24:51.921 --> 01:24:55.062
because Margaret went
to Temple and she's Jewish.

01:24:55.097 --> 01:24:56.862
-(DISHES CLATTER)
-What did you say?

01:24:56.898 --> 01:24:57.930
BARBARA: Excuse me.

01:24:57.965 --> 01:24:59.300
Margaret went to Temple.

01:24:59.335 --> 01:25:00.797
-Okay, Mom, you're done.
-What are you talking about?

01:25:00.832 --> 01:25:02.872
HERB: Okay, that's it.
SYLVIA: Well,
you left the room

01:25:02.907 --> 01:25:04.501
and they're
trying to convert her.

01:25:04.536 --> 01:25:05.970
Well, Margaret has the right
to be baptized

01:25:06.006 --> 01:25:07.107
if she wants to be.

01:25:07.142 --> 01:25:09.074
-Baptized?
-PAUL: If she wants to be.

01:25:09.109 --> 01:25:10.311
BARBARA: I can't believe this.

01:25:11.476 --> 01:25:12.774
I can't believe
you're doing this.

01:25:12.810 --> 01:25:14.644
HERB: All right. Everyone,
this discussion is over.

01:25:14.679 --> 01:25:16.648
We're her parents
and this discussion is over.

01:25:16.684 --> 01:25:18.952
Yeah, you're right, it's over,
because she's already Jewish.

01:25:18.987 --> 01:25:20.485
-Sylvia!
-Well, in our eyes,

01:25:20.521 --> 01:25:24.125
-she's Christian.
-No, no! Margaret is nothing!

01:25:24.161 --> 01:25:27.193
(STUTTERING) Margaret is
not Jewish or Christian.

01:25:27.228 --> 01:25:30.128
She is no religion
until she decides.

01:25:30.163 --> 01:25:31.263
Well, how can she be Jewish

01:25:31.298 --> 01:25:32.794
-if her mother is Christian?
-Stop.

01:25:32.830 --> 01:25:34.702
You were never there for her.
You abandoned her.

01:25:34.738 --> 01:25:35.563
What does it matter?

01:25:35.599 --> 01:25:37.167
Do you think
that we wanted this?

01:25:37.202 --> 01:25:40.442
(OVERLAPPING ARGUMENTS)

01:25:40.477 --> 01:25:41.507
Stop it!

01:25:42.813 --> 01:25:44.342
All of you, just stop it.

01:25:44.377 --> 01:25:47.213
I don't care.
I don't care anymore.

01:25:47.248 --> 01:25:49.684
It's all just
so stupid, religion!

01:25:49.720 --> 01:25:50.951
Just stop fighting!

01:25:50.986 --> 01:25:52.947
I... I don't want a religion.

01:25:52.982 --> 01:25:55.620
-I don't care. I don't care!
-BARBARA: Margaret...

01:25:56.794 --> 01:25:58.755
I don't even believe in God!

01:26:03.127 --> 01:26:04.728
(DOOR SLAMS)

01:26:06.763 --> 01:26:08.831
-Are you happy? Hmm?
-(BARBARA SNIFFLES)

01:26:10.704 --> 01:26:12.734
-I'm so sorry. I did this.
-No, no, no. This is not...

01:26:12.769 --> 01:26:14.342
-I am so sorry.
-No, this is not your fault.

01:26:14.377 --> 01:26:17.244
This is not your fault.
Okay, this is not your fault.

01:26:17.279 --> 01:26:20.044
No, that was everybody else.
That was not...

01:26:20.080 --> 01:26:21.948
-Me.
-No, no, no.

01:26:21.983 --> 01:26:23.681
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

01:26:24.889 --> 01:26:26.552
MARGARET:<i> "Dear Mr. Benedict,</i>

01:26:28.359 --> 01:26:32.558
<i>"what I learned about religion</i>
<i>is that it makes people fight.</i>

01:26:34.693 --> 01:26:37.462
<i>"That every religion</i>
<i>says the same thing.</i>

01:26:37.498 --> 01:26:40.432
<i>"If you pray to God,</i>
<i>he'll listen to you,</i>

01:26:40.467 --> 01:26:42.535
<i>"and help you,</i>
<i>and make things better.</i>

01:26:45.073 --> 01:26:47.438
<i>"But I've prayed and prayed</i>

01:26:47.473 --> 01:26:50.411
<i>"and everything</i>
<i>just gets worse."</i>

01:26:55.445 --> 01:26:57.385
Okay. We'll call you.

01:26:59.653 --> 01:27:01.884
MARGARET:<i> "I don't know</i>
<i>anymore, but I think...</i>

01:27:03.487 --> 01:27:05.756
<i>"that maybe the truth is...</i>

01:27:08.591 --> 01:27:10.365
<i>"there's nobody up there.</i>

01:27:13.266 --> 01:27:15.029
<i>"There's nobody listening.</i>

01:27:18.941 --> 01:27:20.606
<i>"There's only just...</i>

01:27:22.876 --> 01:27:23.972
<i>"me.</i>

01:27:37.059 --> 01:27:40.428
<i>"Sincerely, Margaret Simon."</i>

01:27:46.230 --> 01:27:47.264
Margaret.

01:27:47.300 --> 01:27:49.503
(EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:27:59.783 --> 01:28:01.779
(CRYING SOFTLY)

01:28:21.969 --> 01:28:23.233
(INHALES)

01:28:23.268 --> 01:28:24.901
(EXHALES SHAKILY)

01:28:35.380 --> 01:28:37.353
(STUDENTS CHATTERING)

01:29:08.611 --> 01:29:10.914
-(SIGHS)
-(DOOR SHUTS)

01:29:12.153 --> 01:29:14.382
-BARBARA: Hey.
-Hey.

01:29:14.418 --> 01:29:16.392
Wait. Come here.

01:29:17.689 --> 01:29:19.857
I don't really
feel like talking.

01:29:21.129 --> 01:29:22.695
Yeah. I don't either.

01:29:24.193 --> 01:29:29.669
But, um, I do want to say
sorry for how things went.

01:29:31.904 --> 01:29:36.104
And I know that this past year
has not been easy.

01:29:41.348 --> 01:29:43.111
Want to just sit for a minute?

01:29:57.660 --> 01:30:01.096
Mmm, yeah. Good idea.

01:30:13.617 --> 01:30:17.178
It gets tiring trying so hard
all the time, doesn't it?

01:30:19.217 --> 01:30:20.489
Yeah.

01:30:21.617 --> 01:30:23.921
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

01:30:36.468 --> 01:30:39.035
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

01:30:49.382 --> 01:30:51.586
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:30:55.656 --> 01:30:59.328
-One, two, three. Cheese!
-GIRLS: Cheese!

01:30:59.363 --> 01:31:02.859
-Junior High! Whoo!
-(GRETCHEN CHEERING)

01:31:02.895 --> 01:31:05.798
NANCY: Come on, everybody.
Margaret, come on!

01:31:10.466 --> 01:31:11.672
Hey.

01:31:14.143 --> 01:31:15.236
Thanks, Mr. Benedict.

01:31:16.278 --> 01:31:18.446
You're a really good teacher.

01:31:18.481 --> 01:31:20.481
Well, I wouldn't say all that.
You know,

01:31:20.516 --> 01:31:22.809
still trying to iron out
some of the kinks.

01:31:22.845 --> 01:31:24.817
No, you were really good.

01:31:26.519 --> 01:31:27.919
I'm glad you felt that way.

01:31:28.487 --> 01:31:31.219
(CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:31:45.501 --> 01:31:46.707
Hey.

01:31:49.575 --> 01:31:51.041
Do you want to come dance?

01:31:53.311 --> 01:31:54.649
Really?

01:31:55.379 --> 01:31:56.585
Yeah.

01:32:09.593 --> 01:32:11.165
Yes! I knew it!

01:32:11.201 --> 01:32:12.499
You basically already won.

01:32:12.535 --> 01:32:14.436
GRETCHEN: You've been going
for ages.

01:32:14.471 --> 01:32:16.703
-Ages, Gretchen?
-GRETCHEN: Can I please go?

01:32:16.739 --> 01:32:18.937
NANCY: Gretchen, quit
complaining all the time.

01:32:19.670 --> 01:32:21.038
I'm not complaining.

01:32:21.945 --> 01:32:23.337
(CHEERING)

01:32:26.212 --> 01:32:27.344
Nancy.

01:32:27.380 --> 01:32:28.477
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

01:32:28.513 --> 01:32:29.849
Come on, please?

01:32:35.653 --> 01:32:36.889
GRETCHEN: I got it!

01:32:52.409 --> 01:32:54.876
Really nice work
on the shading, Daniel.

01:32:54.912 --> 01:32:55.806
Thank you.

01:32:55.841 --> 01:32:57.842
I think maybe you could
put a wash here

01:32:57.877 --> 01:33:01.848
just to blend that, but I...
It's beautiful.

01:33:07.488 --> 01:33:10.021
-Oh. Hey, Barbara!
-Jan!

01:33:10.056 --> 01:33:12.458
It's so funny to see you.
I was just gonna call you.

01:33:12.493 --> 01:33:14.259
-Oh.
-Can you believe it,

01:33:14.295 --> 01:33:15.559
about the stars?

01:33:15.594 --> 01:33:17.193
-Oh, I know.
-Jeez.

01:33:17.228 --> 01:33:20.100
Well, I guess everything
is a fire hazard these days.

01:33:20.136 --> 01:33:21.464
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

01:33:21.499 --> 01:33:22.866
Anyway, um,

01:33:22.901 --> 01:33:24.238
we're getting
committees together

01:33:24.273 --> 01:33:25.505
over at the Junior High

01:33:25.541 --> 01:33:26.900
and I can think of
at least three

01:33:26.936 --> 01:33:28.710
that you'd be perfect for.

01:33:28.746 --> 01:33:34.815
Oh, Jan, that sounds great
and I'd love to, but, um...

01:33:36.647 --> 01:33:38.115
I don't want to.

01:33:40.455 --> 01:33:42.553
But thank you for asking me.

01:33:42.588 --> 01:33:45.155
-Yeah.
-And, uh...

01:33:46.263 --> 01:33:47.993
-Have a good day!
-Okay.

01:33:51.363 --> 01:33:52.667
(SIGHS)

01:33:52.703 --> 01:33:54.096
SYLVIA:<i> I'm going to write you</i>
<i>so many letters.</i>

01:33:54.131 --> 01:33:56.699
So many letters,
the mailman's going to say,

01:33:56.734 --> 01:33:58.732
"That's it! No more!"

01:33:58.768 --> 01:34:00.572
(LAUGHING) Okay.

01:34:00.607 --> 01:34:02.708
<i>Oh. Have the best time, honey.</i>

01:34:02.743 --> 01:34:03.871
<i>We'll see you</i>
<i>when you get back.</i>

01:34:03.906 --> 01:34:05.179
See you soon, sweetie.

01:34:05.215 --> 01:34:06.476
-Have fun.
-Bye.

01:34:06.512 --> 01:34:07.947
Love you. Bye!

01:34:10.619 --> 01:34:12.884
-Okay. I think this is it.
-Got it?

01:34:12.920 --> 01:34:14.684
-Then we just have to...
-HERB: Wait, wait, wait.

01:34:14.719 --> 01:34:15.920
-...close it.
-Yeah.

01:34:15.955 --> 01:34:17.787
-Camera, camera, camera.
-MARGARET: Oh, wait.

01:34:17.822 --> 01:34:19.155
-Yes.
-HERB: All right.

01:34:19.190 --> 01:34:21.255
BARBARA: Okay. Now, we just
have to close it.

01:34:21.291 --> 01:34:22.861
